      "writtenOn": "2017-01-18T17:49:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "fDc.r is 8 values (or 4). But they are all the same, yes?\nWondering if we can somehow speed-up by only loading 4 unique values (r, g, b, a) from ctx and then striping them, rather than loading 4*8 values ...",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1008,
        "startChar": 28,
